Usage: createBusGuide [-help] [-type {soft hard}] -netGroup <netGroup> -layer {id | id1:id2} {[{[-centerLine {x1 y1 x2 y2} ] -width <value>} [-beginExt <value>] [-endExt <value>]] | -rect {x1 y1 x2 y2}}

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-beginExt <value>             # user-specified beginning extension, in microns
                              # (float, optional)
-centerLine {x1 y1 x2 y2}     # The coordinate of the center line of the bus
                              # guide segment (box, required)
-endExt <value>               # user-specified end extension, in microns
                              # (float, optional)
-layer {id | id1:id2}         # layer id or a layer range (string, required)
-netGroup <netGroup>          # NetGroup name (string, required)
-rect {x1 y1 x2 y2}           # The rectangle of the bus guide segment with
                              # lower left and upper right coordinates
                              # (box, required)
-type {soft hard}             # Specifies the constraint type of bus guide. If
                              # doesn't use this option to define the
                              # constraint type, the value of constraint type
                              # is soft. (enum, optional)
-width <value>                # width value in microns (float, optional)